    A builder for constructing a LocalConverter.

     

    Note: This builder is not thread safe.

    • Method Detail

      • processTimeout

        public LocalConverter.Builder processTimeout(long processTimeout,
                                             TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Specifies a global timeout for external processes. After the specified amount of milliseconds any conversion process will be killed and the conversion will result with an error. This timeout also applies for starting up or terminating an external converter.
        Parameters:
        processTimeout - The process timeout.
        timeUnit - The time unit of the specified process timeout.
        Returns:
        This builder instance.

      • enable

        public LocalConverter.Builder enable(Class<? extends IExternalConverter> externalConverter)
        Enables the given IExternalConverter. Any converter that is shipped with this library is discovered automatically from the class path and does not need to be enabled explicitly.
        Parameters:
        externalConverter - The converter to be enabled.
        Returns:
        This builder.

      • disable

        public LocalConverter.Builder disable(Class<? extends IExternalConverter> externalConverter)
        Enables the given IExternalConverter. Any converter that is shipped with this library is discovered automatically but can be disabled by invoking this method.
        Parameters:
        externalConverter - The converter to be disabled.
        Returns:
        This builder.
